text: The COVID-19 pandemic was confirmed to have reached the Central African Republic in March 2020. As of 9 April 2020, there were only three ventilators in the entire country. The country's first case was announced on 14 March, with the patient being identified as a 74-year-old Italian man who returned to the Central African Republic from Milan, Italy. ==References== Category:Central African Republic Central African Republic
title: COVID-19 pandemic in the Central African Republic
